   "term": "Design Justice",
   "def": "Design justice, developed by the Design Justice Network and drawn together by Sasha Costanza-Chock (2020), rethinks design to centre people normally marginalized by it. Its principles include centring the voices of those directly impacted, prioritizing impact over the designer's intentions, and treating community-led practice as the way to build technology.",
