   "term": "Reform Versus Real Repair",
   "def": "The working distinction in the resistance week is between a reform and a repair. A reform can leave the harmful system intact while easing its worst edges. A real repair changes who holds power and who carries the cost. Tanksley (2023) models this in education with an abolitionist, critical race pedagogy in computer science.",
