   "term": "AI Governance and Its Gaps",
   "def": "AI governance is the set of laws, rules, and institutions that try to constrain how AI is built and used. AIDA was proposed in 2022 as part of Bill C-27, but parliamentary work ceased in January 2025 and it did not become law. Blair Attard-Frost's 2023 brief argued that the proposal contained five categories of gaps; that was the author's policy analysis, not a court or committee finding.",
